==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fascism
<hw>fasc"ism</hw> <pr>(f⟦acr⟧sh"⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>a political theory advocating an authoritarian hierarchical
government; -- opposed to <contr>democracy</contr> and
<contr>liberalism</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>an authoritarian system of government under absolute
control of a single dictator, allowing no political opposition, forcibly
suppressing dissent, and rigidly controlling most industrial and
economic activities. Such regimes usually try to achieve popularity by a
strongly nationalistic appeal, often mixed with racism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Specifically, the Fascist movement led by
<person>Benito Mussolini</person> in Italy from 1922 to 1943.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>broadly, a tendency toward or support of a strongly
authoritarian or dictatorial control of government or other
organizations; -- often used pejoratively in this sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fascist</ent>⟦br⟧
